# Portfolio Detekcja — Project Standards

Interactive web map for a deep learning engineering thesis on aerial vehicle detection.

**Stack:** Vite, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, OpenLayers, Proj4

## 1. Language Requirements

| Context | Language |
|---------|----------|
| User prompts & agent instructions | English |
| Code: variables, functions, comments | English |
| UI visible in the browser (HTML, buttons, map popups) | Polish |

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
/** Converts WGS84 coordinates to the map's projected CRS. */
function toMapCoordinates(lng: number, lat: number): [number, number] { ... }

const popupContent = `<p>Wykryto pojazd</p>`; // Polish UI text
```

## 2. Modular Architecture

Do not put all logic in `main.ts`. `main.ts` is the entry point only — import and initialize modules.

```
src/
  map/    # OpenLayers init, layers, sources, projections, geospatial logic
  ui/     # DOM components, controls, event listeners
  utils/  # Shared helpers
```

## 3. TypeScript

- Strict TypeScript; never use `any`.
- Explicit return types on functions.
- Define interfaces/types for geospatial data, OpenLayers objects, projections, and configuration.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
function addLayer(map, data) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
interface DetectionFeature {
  id: string;
  coordinates: [number, number];
  confidence: number;
}

function addDetectionLayer(map: Map, features: DetectionFeature[]): void { ... }
```

## 4. Styling

- Use Tailwind utility classes in DOM elements or TypeScript DOM creation.
- Avoid custom CSS in `style.css` unless required for third-party overrides (e.g. OpenLayers controls) or complex animations.

## 5. Clean Code

- Write concise, self-documenting code.
- Add brief JSDoc on complex functions, especially geospatial transformations and spatial data logic.
